  "body": "- [X ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nCan't use unbox on arch and possible debian linux. Because tmp is on tmpfs.\r\nCould possible be avoid by using a smarter move command than fs.rename according to https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4568689/how-do-i-move-file-a-to-a-different-partition-or-device-in-node-js/29287813#29287813 ?\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\ntruffle unbox react-uport   \r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nshould work\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nNot working because not possible to move files. Gives error message\r\n\r\n````bash\r\nu@vivd ~/trufflebox % truffle unbox react-uport           \r\n\r\nDownloading...\r\nevents.js:182\r\n      throw er; // Unhandled 'error' event\r\n      ^\r\n\r\nError: EXDEV: cross-device link not permitted, rename '/home/u/trufflebox/1499850610354-012349819655715244/react-uport-box-master' -> '/tmp/tmp-10479ailj3jPMfbWP/box'\r\n````\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: arch and possible debian, according to some stack overflow links\r\n* Truffle version: 1\r\n* Ethereum client: v3.4.4\r\n* node version: v 8.1.4\r\n* npm version:  5.2.0\r\n",
